  "response_text": "Dear [Student's Name],\n\nI understand that receiving news of a failed exam can be incredibly disappointing and stressful. I want you to know that I am here for you and that your worth is not defined by this single exam result.\n\nFirstly, please remember that setbacks are a natural part of the learning process. Every challenge we face is an opportunity to grow and improve. It\u2019s okay to feel upset or frustrated right now, but it\u2019s also important to take some time to reflect on what happened and how you can use this experience to do better in the future.\n\nIf you need any support or guidance, whether it\u2019s extra help with study materials, advice on test-taking strategies, or just someone to talk to, please don\u2019t hesitate to reach out. Your teachers and I are here to support you every step of the way.\n\nRemember, your intelligence and potential extend far beyond one exam. You have shown resilience and determination in other areas of your life, and I have no doubt that you will continue",
